rors of commonly used\napproximations in the literature. Easy-to-use tools like MADCUBA allow the\nusers to derive the physical information from spectroscopic data without the\nneed of resourcing to simple approximations. SLIM allows to use the full\nradiative transfer equation, and to interactively explore the space of physical\nparameters and associated uncertainties from observational data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Sep 2019 23:10:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-13"}
