tised model may be\nobservable in all-sky observations made by WMAP and Planck, the recently\nlaunched eROSITA, the Fermi-LAT, and ground-based observations by HESS, HAWC,\nand the forthcoming CTA. The non-thermal emissions predicted by the discretised\nmodel may also provide explanations of puzzling anomalies in high-energy gamma\nray data, such as the Fermi-LAT north/south asymmetry and residuals like the\nso-called \"Fermi bubbles\".\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Sep 2019 06:19:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 31 Dec 2019 17:58:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-08"}
